definition.value: The calcium salt of (2xi)-D-gluco-heptonic acid. It is used as a calcium supplement for treatment of hypocalcaemia.
A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from dichromic acid.
A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of one of the two OH groups in dichromic acid.
A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of one of the two OH groups in chromic acid.
An acene that consists of five ortho-fused benzene rings in a rectilinear arrangement.
An acene that consists of six ortho-fused benzene rings in a rectilinear arrangement.
An acene that consists of seven ortho-fused benzene rings in a rectilinear arrangement.
A medium-chain fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of obtusilic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A medium-chain, unsaturated, straight-chain fatty acid anion and the conjugate base of  dec-9-enoic acid (caproleic acid), arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A metal iodide salt with a Na(+) counterion.
The hydrochloride salt of atomoxetine.
An acene that consists of nine ortho-fused benzene rings in a rectilinear arrangement.
A tetrazocane that is 1,3,5,7-tetrazocane in which the hydrogen atom attached to each of the nitrogens is replaced by a nitro group.
A fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any long-chain (C13 to C22) fatty acid.
A dinitrile that is methane substituted by two cyano groups.

A calcheamicin in which contains 3-O-methyl-alpha-L-rhamnosyl, 2,6-dideoxy-4-thio-beta-D-ribo-hexopyranosyl, and 4-amino-4,6-dideoxy-2-O-[2,4-dideoxy-4-(ethylamino)-3-O-methyl-alpha-L-threo-pentopyranosyl]-alpha-L-idopyranose units and in which the aromatic ring contains an iodo substituent.
A cyanide salt containing equal numbers of potassium cations and cyanide anions.
A cyanide salt containing equal numbers of sodium cations and cyanide anions.
A tetrazole tautomer where the proton is located on the 1st position.
A tetrazole tautomer where the proton is located on the 2 position.
